Market Leadership: North America holds a significant share of the traveling wave fault location device market, driven by substantial investments in power infrastructure and a strong focus on grid modernization.
Technological Advancements: The region is at the forefront of adopting advanced fault detection technologies, with utilities increasingly integrating these devices into their operations to enhance grid reliability.
